/* ═══ CONFETTI — flakes drifting down BOTH side gutters, never the lane
   (fine features stay at the edges: L6). Each gutter stacks TWO independent
   layers (a sparse bright NEAR field + a fine dense FAR field of circles,
   streamers and tumbling squares in the show palette). Smooth LINEAR fall
   with a gentle wind-sway — NO steps() — so it never stutters. The two
   gutters run different prime-ish durations (19s / 25s) with a negative
   delay on the right, so the left and right patterns never sync or visibly
   repeat. The tile is 50vh and the box overscans, so a 50vh translate loops
   seamlessly. Continuous movers → will-change: transform (2 of 3). ═══ */
